{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_36","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job for `org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20` failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1559-library-new-request-org.projectlombok-lombok-1.18.20-c6ba61e1\n\nThe most likely failing stage was post-generation test/native validation, not artifact discovery or URL population. Evidence: `human-intervention-logs/org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` both end with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, and the generated test suite reached 25/25 dynamic-access coverage (100%). However, the generator log `human-intervention-logs/org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T01-06-33-811043Z.log` shows the final coverage commit (`7fe7ddda`) was produced without compiling or running tests.\n\nThe native test output points to Lombok-specific runtime/resource behavior as the blocker. In `tests/src/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`, `ShadowClassLoaderTest` aborts because native image does not expose shadow-loader resources as enumerable jar/file URLs, and `AgentTest` aborts with `IllegalArgumentException: Unknown protocol: resource:/lombok/launch/Agent.class`. The follow-up log `human-intervention-logs/org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows extra manual work was then needed to add shadow-loader reflection/resource metadata plus predefined classes (`predefined-classes-config.json` and 79 `.classdata` files) before a focused `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20 --stacktrace` run became green.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T01-01-01-546648Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T01-06-33-811043Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20/metadata-fix/codex.log`\n- `tests/src/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Review the preserved branch and decide whether to keep the added metadata/predefined-classes files and the native-specific test adjustments.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20 --stacktrace` and `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20 --stacktrace`.\n3. If skipped native tests are not acceptable for a new-library request, replace those assertions with coverage that works under native-image `resource:` URL semantics."}}
